  <entry xml:base="http://www.mapdb.org/blog/atom.xml">
    <title type="text">Memory mapped file and JVM crash</title>
    <id>http://www.mapdb.org/news/mmap_file_and_jvm_crash/</id>
    <updated>2016-04-23T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <published>2016-04-23T00:00:00Z</published>
    <link href="http://www.mapdb.org/news/mmap_file_and_jvm_crash/" />
    <author>
      <name>Jan</name>
    </author>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Memory mapped (mmap) file reatly improves performance over traditional &lt;code class=&quot;docutils literal&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pre&quot;&gt;RandomAccessFile&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code class=&quot;docutils literal&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;pre&quot;&gt;FileChannel&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;.
However it has quirks and could cause JVM crash. MapDB contains some workarounds to make it more stable.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
